Program: Great Lives
Title: Sara Pascoe on Virginia Woolf
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b07npxx3
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 19 Aug 2016
Sara Pascoe champions the life of Virginia Woolf, author of 'Mrs Dalloway' and 'A Room of One's Own', describing her as a sensible feminist. Sara explains why she thinks if she were alive today, Woolf would be a comedian, and how through her diaries and letters she's discovered the witty, manic and egotistical Virginia. Presenter Matthew Parris confesses to struggling with her work. Alexandra Harris is the expert. Producer: Toby Field. Show less